House Resolution 96
By: Representatives Moore of the 91st and Crawford of the 89th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing Dr. Gregory B. Levett, Sr., and dedicating a road in his honor; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Dr. Gregory B. Levett, Sr., has long been recognized for his expertise as a
4 mortician and funeral director and the compassionate role he has played during the most
5 difficult time of a family's life; and
6 WHEREAS, Dr. Levett and his wife, Betty, founded the world renowned Gregory B. Levett
7 & Sons Funeral Homes & Crematory in 1980, growing the business to serve over 2,300
8 families a year, employing 175 full and part-time employees, with four locations and an
9 off-site crematory; and
10 WHEREAS, Dr. Levett began mastering the art of funeral service at a young age after being
11 introduced to the industry by his father, the late George W. Levett, Sr.; and
12 WHEREAS, the Levett legacy of providing traditional, thoughtful, and dignified funeral
13 services spans over four generations, with Dr. Levett passing on his knowledge and love of
14 caring for others to his children, Gregory Bernard, Jr., T. Lanier, and Deana, who are all
15 active in the daily operations of the business; and
