16 WHEREAS, his leadership and guidance have been instrumental to numerous organizations,
17 including the National Funeral Directors and Morticians Association, Georgia Funeral
18 Service Practitioners Association, DeKalb Chapter of the 100 Black Men of America, City
19 of Decatur Public School Board Council, NAACP, Salem Gate Merchants Association,
20 DeKalb Parks and Recreation Committee Board of Directors, Scottdale Planning Council,
21 South DeKalb Business League, as well as the DeKalb Chamber of Commerce, Gwinnett
22 Chamber of Commerce, Rockdale Chamber of Commerce, and the Georgia Hispanic
23 Chamber of Commerce; and
24 WHEREAS, Dr. Levett has been recognized with numerous awards and honors, including
25 a Lifetime Achievement Award from President Barack Obama for his volunteer services,
26 Funeral Director of the Year from American Funeral Director Magazine in 2015, and the
27 Robert H. Miller Funeral Director of the Year in 2023; and
28 WHEREAS, the Levett family has donated over $2 million to institutions of higher learning,
29 churches, hospitals, charities, and community organizations, with Emory Hillandale Hospital
30 dedicating a reception area of the emergency department to honor Dr. Levett and his wife;
31 and
32 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the extraordinary accomplishments of
33 this distinguished Georgian be appropriately recognized by dedicating a road in his honor.
34 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED AND ENACTED BY THE GENERAL
35 ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA that the portion of State Route 155 from I-285 to Snapfinger
36 Road in DeKalb County is dedicated as the Dr. Gregory B. Levett, Sr. Parkway.
